For this, we will solve for the present value of the annual perpetuity which is given as:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Present value of annual perpetuity}&=\dfrac{\text{Cash flow}}{\text{Interest rate}}\\[15 pt]
&=\dfrac{\$35,000}{\text{r}}
\end{aligned}$$

Since we cannot solve for this fully, we will leave this as is.
